USA: Repetition is the mother of wisdom
It is almost strange with what student ardentness Barack Obama, the president with his reputation as the smartest, repeats his predecessor's strategy on the Afghanistan issue, which he himself considered to be the dumbest.
When he finally sweated out his eagerly awaited Afghanistan doctrine, it turned out that he wrote it about the copy paper from the Bush Iraq scenario three years ago.
Not only did he use the phrase "as in Iraq" several times in the text itself, he even used the name of the Bush Declaration of January 2007 as the name of his own declaration: "New Forward Way" without squandering.
Three years ago, he himself criticized the Bush idea of sending out fresh contingents of troops to Iraq, which was plagued by the civil war, as an "irresponsible and in its conclusions atrocious decision".
However, the following months showed that the Bush strategy, based on military recommendations, was the only possible and very successful, and that today the news about Iraq no longer speaks at all.
This did not improve Bush’s reputation, for objectively, he left his successor with a much more grateful initial situation than was expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes that the miracle will be repeated.
The military once again asked him to increase the contingent of troops, especially the chief commander of the Afghanistan operation General Stanley McCristal, who, despite his subordination habits, severely criticized the squandering shooters in the White House.
He called for 40,000 soldiers to reverse the situation for the better.
The president hesitated for three months, but he didn't come up with a better idea, so he betrayed the general wenist by 10,000 soldiers.
From Europe, he has pressed the promise for another 5,000, even though he himself originally expected at least 10,000.
Most problematic about the entire Obama strategy is his intention to withdraw troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and complete this process within three years.The entire Obama doctrine leaves more questions than answers.
Some doubt that the halved increase will have the same effect as the measure in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal war of recent years, the Iraqi society is relatively well structured, its leaders honor the values.
The Afghan situation is marked by the contraindication - no one can rely on it and no agreements are kept.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces who are used to changing their minds every day.
The political institutions, even if they were formally established correctly, remain only sham buildings behind which patriarchal tribal relations will continue to grow.
The balance of interests between the various ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially because of the complexity of the conditions that complicate the Pakistan and Iran influences even further.
The construction of a "workable state", which is the minimalist goal of the entire operation, is also very unrealistic.
Time horizon of Obama’s strategy alienated by its voluntarism
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only deteriorated further and now it is on the brink of the explosion.
To believe that the little soldiers, who broke out into the war cry about the "early homecoming", create a miracle here, can only be a truly romantic soul that cannot be impressed by facts.
From a political point of view, the date for the withdrawal of troops is irresponsibility, because the Taliban will accept this as the indirect confession of American defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that Europeans’ willingness to participate in the battles in Afghanistan is running out.
Europe's politicians cannot and do not want to explain to their voters how the security of Germany or Italy is linked to the war in the Hindu Kush foothills.
Another possible factor that can radically influence the situation is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and the increased sanctions do not affect the Iranians, a very serious question arises for the United States as to whether the problem cannot be solved with troops.
This question needs to be answered during the period when America is moving to the victory withdrawal from Afghanistan after Obama.
However, any solution will also mean a dramatic turn of the Afghan situation.
The only consolation for Barack Obama is the fact that three years remain until the presidential election, and so there is still enough time left for him to take a different strategy, which would turn out to be a total failure.
