The fact that the future economic direction of the great world powers is at stake has broken out within the industrialized nations as well as between the industrialized nations and the emerging economies.
The current struggle refers equally to saving individual economies, as well as saving the planet, with China and the United States fighting for their corresponding commitments, while poorer countries claim that the two dozen most influential countries would ignore the scientific need to take bolder action.
Ricardo Ulate, a delegate from Costa Rica, said that it is not surprising that the big powers are struggling to find out who should bear the cost of curbing greenhouse gas emissions, as even affected countries have gone over to act more aggressively to hold the countries with very high greenhouse gas emissions accountable for their actions.
