After a three-week negotiating marathon, the unions of the street association and the TLF - the only employer organization that remained until the end - came to an agreement on Friday evening that put an end to the strike order and the impending severe supply shortage at Christmas.
At the signature meeting on Friday evening, the Secretary of State responsible for transport Dominique Bussereau "welcomed" the agreement, which was launched on Wednesday morning after several weeks of negotiations.
